Mozilla Festival is three days of hands-on building, bold conversation, and ideas worth traveling for. Every year, thousands of technologists, artists, journalists, policymakers, and activists come together to imagine, and actively build, a better digital world.

The 2026 theme is Wilding, inspired by the ecological practice of rewilding. It's a call to return to the edges of what technology can be: to claim the systems we build and the infrastructures they run on, and to experiment with models rooted in agency, mutuality, and collective intelligence.

Mozilla Festival 2026 is part of Open Tech Week, hosted in partnership with the City of Barcelona. The festival program is co-created with community curators from around the world. Workshops, performances, labs, and conversations fill the program across technology, art, policy, and culture.

Early bird tickets are on sale now. The Call for Proposals opens in May 2026.
